<br>
*shrugs*<br>
<br>
Lucky me, that he never hit. Double death would suck, especially at the high levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucoinfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coinfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/14/02 11:38:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2546.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What the heck is &quot;pain and suffering&quot;, exactly</span><hr size=1> Pain and suffering is what you get when you are stabbed with a long pointed object.  However, this can also occur when you fall a long distance and even short distances onto sharp objects.  There are more ways but those are some of the common ones.<br>
<br>
Coinfist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=illudin>Illudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/02 12:58:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2546.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What the heck is &quot;pain and suffering&quot;, exactly</span><hr size=1> I seem to recall &quot;pain and suffering&quot; being the generic damage source for DoTs when you have one on you and you cross zones or fall unconscious. I believe it might also be the generic damage source for blood loss. Of course, I haven't seen either one do that in a very long while...<br>
<br>
